<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 26 at 4:16AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...AREAS OF DENSE FOG THIS MORNING...
Areas of fog will persist across the region through the late
morning hours. Fog may become dense in some locations, leading to
visibility of one quarter mile or less. With temperatures below
freezing, fog may lead to some icy spots on area roadways.
Drivers should be prepared for rapidly fluctuating visibilities
and the possibility of variable roadway conditions. Slow down and
allow plenty of distance between you and the vehicle in front of
you.</description>
